This webpage is intended to inform Agency representatives on stage elevation in the various waterbodies within the Everglades Region (North and South).

Please note this analysis is using preliminary data and subject to change.

Kissimmee Chain-of-Lakes

Kissimmee Chain-of-Lakes with structures and lakes identified.

Kissimmee Chain-of-Lakes relative to each respective regulation schedule.
Data are provisional and subject to change.



Lake Okeechobee

Lake Okeechobee with stage monitoring points and inflow structures identified.

Lake Okeechobee daily average stage elevation (red line) relative to the Lake Okeechobee Regulation Schedule (LORS). Mean stage is calculated using data from L001, L005, L006, LZ40, S4TW,S352HW, S308HW & S133TW.
Data are provisional and subject to change.



Rotenberger and Holey Land Wildlife Management Areas

Rotenberger and Holey Land Wildlife Management Areas with stage monitoring points and inflow structures identified.(STAs=Stormwater Treatment Areas; RS= Restoration Strategies; EvPA=Everglades Protection Area)

Mean stage elevation for Rotenberger (RotenN and RotenS) and Holey Land (G-203D) Wildlife Management Areas relative to water management schedules.Note the regulation schedule for Holey Land WMA is a proposed water management schedule and has not been reviewed or approved by FDEP.
Data are provisional and subject to change.
